1
00:00:00,070 --> 00:00:02,930
[Emergency Medical Center]

2
00:00:17,850 --> 00:00:19,310
Prosecutor Ju, move!

3
00:00:39,470 --> 00:00:40,520
Lee Chaeha,

4
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,430
are you crazy?

5
00:00:42,570 --> 00:00:44,100
Who allowed you to get hurt?

6
00:00:45,220 --> 00:00:47,210
I was afraid you'd get hurt.

7
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,680
Who do you think you are?

8
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:52,510
I'm your investigator.

9
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:02,500
Damn it.

10
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:04,010
Are you okay?

11
00:01:04,129 --> 00:01:05,129
Does it hurt a lot?

12
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,660
What did the doctor say?

13
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:07,910
Will it leave a scar?

14
00:01:08,539 --> 00:01:12,140
The doctor said fortunately,
it wasn't deep, so it's no big deal.

15
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:17,200
Don't get hurt by other people.

16
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,700
Be it physically or mentally.

17
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,010
Huh?

18
00:01:22,370 --> 00:01:24,990
It's enough
that I'm the only one hurting you.

19
00:01:25,630 --> 00:01:27,430
More than enough.

20
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:31,130
Ah... Where's Han Soojin?

21
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:33,990
Is that what's important to you right now?

22
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:37,900
Then what is important to us?

23
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,759
She's already been detained
at the district prosecutor's detention center.

24
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:43,500
You should hurry home and rest.

25
00:01:43,890 --> 00:01:45,700
We need to interrogate Han Soojin first...

26
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:47,490
It's not a request, but a command.

27
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:48,490
Do as you're told.

28
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:50,190
Have you forgotten already?

29
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:51,780
What about that kid?

30
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,930
He is also safe.

31
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:58,320
Let's go. I'll take you home.

32
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:37,530
[Uncle]

33
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:38,329
[Remind Me]

34
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:44,290
Chaeha, please answer the phone.

35
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:44,290
[Chaeha, please answer the phone.]

36
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:46,790
Do you know Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho?

37
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,790
[Chaeha,
do you know Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho?]

38
00:02:46,790 --> 00:02:50,430
[Chaeha, if this continues, I'll die.]

39
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,070
Pick up the phone, you brat.

40
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:49,960
If this continues, I'll die.

41
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:52,050
Hey, Lee Chaeha!

42
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:52,050
[Hey, Lee Chaeha!]

43
00:02:52,210 --> 00:02:53,190
[Slide to power off]

44
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,690
It's enough that
I'm the only one hurting you.

45
00:03:05,070 --> 00:03:07,240
More than enough.

46
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,700
A complete psycho.

47
00:03:15,580 --> 00:03:17,120
Am I a pervert?

48
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:21,010
[Park Siwoo]

49
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:25,940
[Kim Yunsik]

50
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:32,950
[Kwak Seunghwan]
[Because of inheritance?]

51
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:35,190
[Koryoin Mr. Kim overdosed on drugs]

52
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:37,030
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

53
00:03:37,329 --> 00:03:39,150
[The Last Abandoned Mine in Danhyeon City
To Be Turned Into a Casino]

54
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:42,140
[Led by Ohsong Construction, 'Danhyeon Land' Integrated Resort (Casino, Hotel, Theme Park) to be built—
Officially secures $400M in foreign investment]

55
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:46,730
[Casino Industry's First Female Executive…
Pledges "Transparent Operations, Regional Co-Prosperity"]

56
00:03:46,730 --> 00:03:48,430
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
the suspect is his driver, Lee]

57
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:57,329
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

58
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:59,579
[Prosecutor's Office]

59
00:04:04,810 --> 00:04:05,830
Prosecutor Ju.

60
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,960
Oh Jayeon's blood test came back positive.

61
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,900
It's probably meth.

62
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:12,880
Did you get some good rest?

63
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:13,650
Yeah.

64
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:16,870
If we compare the composition model
with Koryoin Kim's,

65
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:19,459
we should be able to find out
if the drugs came from the same source.

66
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:20,940
He's already been cremated.

67
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:23,670
Right. The body was
not claimed by any relatives.

68
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:25,290
I was careless.

69
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:28,290
I should have moved first
to stop the cremation.

70
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:43,920
How can I help you?

71
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:47,440
I'm here to turn myself in.

72
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,400
Something's off.

73
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:58,260
Why is it that right when
we are investigating Oh Jayeon's blood,

74
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,870
the killer turns himself in?

75
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:02,870
This decision must have been
outside their original plan.

76
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,240
If I hadn't insisted,

77
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,920
the case of Koryoin Kim

78
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:09,190
would have quickly been closed
as an accidental death with no indictment.

79
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:10,690
Plan?

80
00:05:11,530 --> 00:05:14,330
Is Oh Jayeon really related to this case?

81
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,630
Let's go.

82
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:23,940
Where to?

83
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,660
A motel.

84
00:05:27,290 --> 00:05:28,460
What?

85
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:32,460
In broad daylight?

86
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:36,300
[Lizzy Motel]

87
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:37,530
P-Prosecutor Ju.

88
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,270
I don't think this is a good idea.

89
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:41,130
It's not night yet.

90
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,300
It's not night yet?

91
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,210
Are you saying it's fine at night, then?

92
00:05:46,710 --> 00:05:47,909
That's not what I—

93
00:06:09,170 --> 00:06:09,990
Ah.

94
00:06:12,220 --> 00:06:13,250
[Public Official ID: Ju Taeseon,
Supreme Prosecutors' Office]

95
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:16,490
Excuse me.

96
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:20,360
Do you know this person?

97
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,540
Yes, I know him.

98
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:26,510
Was it a month ago?

99
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:29,230
He stuttered a bit
and showed a Russian passport,

100
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:30,570
so I remember him.

101
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:33,670
But he looked very much like a Korean.

102
00:06:34,909 --> 00:06:37,040
Can you tell me which room he stayed in?

103
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:37,880
Hold on.

104
00:06:38,110 --> 00:06:39,070
Be good.

105
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:46,480
[January 9, Room 603, Aleksandr]

106
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,550
Room 603.

107
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,070
Did he stay here for only one day
and leave?

108
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:50,520
No.

109
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,070
He checked in,

110
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:55,270
but he came out shortly after.

111
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:57,380
And then he never came back.

112
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:58,900
Damn it.

113
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:01,810
He didn't even return the room key.

114
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:04,230
When I saw him leaving
with a suitcase that day,

115
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:05,600
I should have known.

116
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:07,470
Can we go in and take a look?

117
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:08,710
Sure.

118
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:16,880
Thank you.

119
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:46,400
Why did he have to come to this motel
right across from the casino?

120
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,060
He obviously never came back—

121
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,360
why did he leave after just a short while?

122
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,240
What exactly did he do here?

123
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:05,390
What else can you do in a place like this?

124
00:08:07,690 --> 00:08:08,670
What?

125
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:11,340
Do you think I'm going to eat you up?

126
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:12,620
Don't worry.

127
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,560
I separate personal
and professional matters.

128
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,690
Huh?

129
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:24,190
Over there.

130
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,140
Is there something?

131
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,340
There's something...

132
00:08:58,810 --> 00:09:00,340
There is indeed something.

133
00:09:00,860 --> 00:09:02,140
What is this?

134
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,330
That's right.

135
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,520
It's drugs.

136
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,800
Why are there drugs here?

137
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,060
He must have swapped them in advance.

138
00:09:31,190 --> 00:09:33,770
Wow, he swapped a lot.

139
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:37,690
We got a recording...

140
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:43,020
We'll go to the National Forensic Service tomorrow
and request an expedited analysis of the drug composition.

141
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:45,500
If it matches the drugs
found in Oh Jayeon's body,

142
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,430
we have to apply
for an arrest warrant immediately.

143
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:48,870
Will the higher-ups approve it?

144
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:51,730
Verifying her drug use is enough.

145
00:09:52,010 --> 00:09:55,680
After all, we can only
get something out of her if we detain her.

146
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:57,670
Speaking of,

147
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,360
she must have been furious—

148
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:03,560
getting fewer drugs than agreed upon.

149
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,330
Is that why she killed him?

150
00:10:06,690 --> 00:10:07,610
No.

151
00:10:07,810 --> 00:10:09,070
What is certain is that

152
00:10:09,110 --> 00:10:10,720
he died because
the drugs burst in his stomach.

153
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,460
We also found plastic fragments.

154
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:14,540
But I still feel something is off.

155
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:16,750
Logically speaking,

156
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:19,360
Oh Jayeon killed him out of anger.

157
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,200
Could it be that
Oh Jayeon pried his mouth open

158
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,060
and forced him
to swallow the plastic bag?

159
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:25,720
Then there should be
bruises around his lips.

160
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:32,130
His face was flawless too...

161
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,790
Except for that needle mark on his neck.

162
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,410
Let's eat first. I'm hungry.

163
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:40,530
Sure.

164
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,800
Didn't you say you were hungry?

165
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:05,380
Swallow your food before you speak.

166
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,400
Didn't you say you were hungry?

167
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:10,400
I am hungry, so I'm eating, aren't I?

168
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:13,300
Eat slowly.

169
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:17,360
Are you slowing down for me?

170
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:19,890
Don't be curious about useless things.

171
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:23,650
Let's assume Oh Jayeon has some connection
to the Koryoin, Mr. Kim.

172
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,250
If things go well,

173
00:11:25,570 --> 00:11:28,250
she'll be arrested
for abandoning the body.

174
00:11:28,380 --> 00:11:29,920
Then, if we find more evidence,

175
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,050
she can be sentenced, right?

176
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:34,380
Could she have done all this alone?

177
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,170
Probably not.

178
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:41,740
Will Ohsong Construction help cover it up?

179
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,700
After all, they wouldn't want
to taint the family name.

180
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,040
Maybe.

181
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,120
The old man who turned himself in
for killing the Koryoin, Mr. Kim,

182
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,060
was there anything suspicious
in his call logs?

183
00:11:52,060 --> 00:11:52,930
No.

184
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:55,160
Check the Koryoin's call logs

185
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:57,310
from near where his body was dumped.

186
00:11:57,330 --> 00:11:58,930
Okay, got it.

187
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,240
Who could've helped Oh Jayeon?

188
00:12:10,190 --> 00:12:12,690
[Investigator Song Haneul: Where are you?]

189
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,550
Where are you?

190
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:15,270
[Investigator Song Haneul: Where are you?
Investigator Song Haneul: Want to grab a meal together?]

191
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:15,270
Want to grab a meal together?

192
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:16,780
Who is it?

193
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:18,380
Your uncle?

194
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,500
No.

195
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:22,620
Then?

196
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:25,350
It's Section Chief Song.

197
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:29,350
Seems like you two are quite close.

198
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,630
He takes good care of me.

199
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:34,460
Sounds good.

200
00:12:36,350 --> 00:12:38,080
Let's go if you're done eating.

201
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:47,140
Prosecutor Ju!

202
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:52,610
[Prosecutor's Office]

203
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:05,050
Uncle.

204
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:07,340
Why didn't you answer my calls?

205
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,670
Chaeha.

206
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:14,340
The Western District Office
is suddenly investigating me,

207
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:17,080
saying my laundry shop

208
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:19,980
is involved in bribery, embezzlement,
and malpractice.

209
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:21,880
Damn it, I've got
a splitting headache right now.

210
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,740
One wrong move, and my company...

211
00:13:23,850 --> 00:13:25,290
will be gone.

212
00:13:28,090 --> 00:13:29,870
Please help me.

213
00:13:30,450 --> 00:13:33,130
Who is the prosecutor you work with?

214
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:42,220
Excuse me.

215
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:44,720
Are you Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho?

216
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:47,000
I am Ju Taeseon.

217
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,870
Ah, yes.

218
00:13:57,530 --> 00:14:00,240
Go to Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho

219
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:02,210
and put in a good word for me.

220
00:14:02,530 --> 00:14:03,710
Okay?

221
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:06,290
You should know,
if you don't resolve this,

222
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:09,620
your aunt, me,
and our whole family will be ruined

223
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,960
because of you.

224
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:14,500
Did you do something wrong?

225
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:19,510
Damn it!
Is that what's important right now?

226
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,930
You brat,
after I raised you all these years...

227
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:25,730
You're biting the hand that feeds you.

228
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:28,390
Is this how you repay me for raising you?
Damn it—

229
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:39,540
My investigator is very busy.

230
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:42,850
It was nice

231
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:44,820
to see you again.

232
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:06,360
Don't get hurt by other people.

233
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:08,780
Be it physically or mentally.

234
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,770
Section Chief Song.

235
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:12,720
Hmm?

236
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,050
Do you know Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho?

237
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:16,590
Yeah, I know him.

238
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:19,530
Is he close with Prosecutor Ju?

239
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:26,540
Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho
and Prosecutor Yoon Soyeon are twins—

240
00:15:26,710 --> 00:15:27,790
fraternal twins.

241
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:31,670
Prosecutor Ju was quite close
to Prosecutor Yoon Soyeon.

242
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:34,160
But I'm not so sure about now—

243
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,200
since Prosecutor Yoon Soyeon
committed suicide.

244
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:41,470
Ah, I was just curious
if they were close.

245
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,210
Hard to say.

246
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:45,020
Why?

247
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:47,050
Just curious.

248
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,260
Mr. Lee, do you not have any siblings?

249
00:15:57,230 --> 00:15:58,870
Yeah.

250
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:01,980
Did you go out to do fieldwork
with Prosecutor Ju today?

251
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:03,070
Yeah.

252
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:04,530
Have you had lunch?

253
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:05,740
Yeah.

254
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:07,640
Do you want to watch a movie this weekend?

255
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:08,680
Yeah.

256
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:09,780
Huh?

257
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:12,080
You just agreed to it.

258
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,870
The results are out.

259
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:52,650
The drugs found in the motel
and those in Oh Jayeon's blood test

260
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,900
are both meth.

261
00:17:12,770 --> 00:17:14,089
Be more mindful.

262
00:17:14,990 --> 00:17:17,599
Only Section Chief Song is outside.

263
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:25,770
[Drug Analysis Report]

264
00:17:25,770 --> 00:17:28,730
[The drug components detected in Exhibit 1 and Exhibit 2
were both confirmed to be methamphetamine.]

265
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:30,710
Koryoin Kim must have made a trade
with Oh Jayeon.

266
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:34,280
I also resubmitted
the glove found at the scene for testing.

267
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:37,330
Didn't they already check it
and find nothing?

268
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:39,660
Last time, they only checked the surface.

269
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:43,340
I asked them to shred it and test
the DNA on the cross-section this time.

270
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:44,240
Oh.

271
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,090
This too.

272
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:54,960
The last four digits are 1225.

273
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,040
Christmas.

274
00:17:57,230 --> 00:18:00,470
There was a cell tower ping on the night
the Koryoin's body was dumped.

275
00:18:00,470 --> 00:18:02,710
There was also a record
left near the motel.

276
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:07,170
The phone number is registered to a Russian,
but the person is not in the country.

277
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:11,280
A burner phone registered under a Russian.

278
00:18:11,620 --> 00:18:15,290
Currently, the application
for Oh Jayeon's search warrant,

279
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:17,330
as well as the arrest warrant,

280
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:19,490
will be handled by Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho.

281
00:18:19,490 --> 00:18:20,940
Prosecutor Yoon?

282
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,130
Yeah.

283
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:26,600
I was afraid of a connection
to Lee Gilyoung arising midway.

284
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,460
If anything goes wrong,

285
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:31,280
you might become a related party.

286
00:18:31,490 --> 00:18:34,320
So it's safer to have Prosecutor Yoon
assist with the investigation.

287
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:38,370
His sister
is Prosecutor Yoon Soyeon, right?

288
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,520
When did you find out about this?

289
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:43,270
That's right.

290
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,240
So, like us,

291
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:49,180
he has a motive to properly investigate
the Ohsong people.

292
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:53,230
After all, Soyeon also passed away
halfway through the investigation.

293
00:18:53,540 --> 00:18:54,950
Anyway,

294
00:18:55,330 --> 00:18:57,450
he is not a related party,

295
00:18:57,590 --> 00:19:00,450
and is exactly who we need
investigating this case.

296
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:06,220
The Western District Office
is suddenly investigating me.

297
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:09,440
Go to Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho

298
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:11,710
and put in a good word for me.

299
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:18,480
Are you close enough with him
to ask him for a personal favor?

300
00:19:20,170 --> 00:19:21,310
No.

301
00:19:26,030 --> 00:19:28,800
Are you curious about how close we are?

302
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,970
Now is probably not the time
to ask about such personal matters.

303
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:39,080
So what happens after applying
for Oh Jayeon's arrest warrant?

304
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,340
We have to go meet the reference witness,

305
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:42,500
Oh Miyeon.

306
00:19:43,690 --> 00:19:45,430
Oh Miyeon...

307
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:48,040
The current chairman of Ohsong,

308
00:19:48,170 --> 00:19:50,290
Oh Jayeon's older sister.

309
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:55,180
Then she might know
who is helping Oh Jayeon.

310
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:57,720
We'll know after hearing
what she has to say.

311
00:19:58,980 --> 00:20:01,070
I need to meet Prosecutor Yoon.

312
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:04,720
Let's meet in the parking lot
in half an hour.

313
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,450
Okay, got it.

314
00:20:22,690 --> 00:20:24,020
Hello. Thank you for your hard work.

315
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:26,460
This is Prosecutor Ju Taeseon's office.

316
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:28,300
I'd like to ask you to check

317
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,410
the glove we asked you
to run a DNA test on last time.

318
00:20:30,410 --> 00:20:33,420
What? An arrest warrant for Oh Jayeon?

319
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:34,510
You want me to request it?

320
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:35,560
Yeah.

321
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:39,370
She is suspected of violating
the Narcotics Control Act and abandoning a corpse.

322
00:20:39,370 --> 00:20:41,300
We probably need to detain her
before investigating further.

323
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,690
Where is the evidence?

324
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:44,430
Are you sure?

325
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:49,800
Without evidence, I dare not flash
an arrest warrant at a casino director.

326
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,400
This is the result of my hard work
over the past few days.

327
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,250
I'll leave the procedures to you.

328
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,980
As for the interrogation,
I want to take the lead.

329
00:21:00,450 --> 00:21:02,900
Why do you do all the hard work

330
00:21:02,110 --> 00:21:03,990
[Drug Analysis Report]

331
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:04,860
and give all the credit to me?

332
00:21:03,990 --> 00:21:05,250
[Autopsy Report]

333
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:07,490
This is a good scenario, though.

334
00:21:08,570 --> 00:21:09,590
But why?

335
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:10,830
Hmm?

336
00:21:11,260 --> 00:21:12,880
Why are you giving me this for free?

337
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,860
I'm returning the favor from last time.

338
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:18,450
What? That important person
from last time?

339
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:23,320
That wasn't anything difficult, but you are
returning such a big favor.

340
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:26,280
After all,
there was what happened to Soyeon, too.

341
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:28,470
What I want is revenge.

342
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:32,600
What about the communication records
between the drug dealer and Oh Jayeon?

343
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,180
I've checked everything.

344
00:21:34,570 --> 00:21:37,130
Both of them used burner phones.
I couldn't find anything.

345
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:38,920
On the day the Koryoin's body was dumped,

346
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:43,450
a suspicious number, 1225,
was found at a nearby base station.

347
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:46,420
But there was no other discovery.

348
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:52,420
But if we charge Oh Jayeon with violating the Narcotics Control Act
and abandoning a corpse,

349
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:53,250
[Drug Analysis Report]

350
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:55,770
the sentence in the first trial
probably won't be high.

351
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:58,600
No matter how much we investigate,
she won't even get 10 years.

352
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,070
About that...

353
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:03,530
This matter is somewhat related
to some other cases.

354
00:22:03,660 --> 00:22:06,060
What? Some other cases?

355
00:22:09,140 --> 00:22:10,150
Come in.

356
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,440
Both of you are here?

357
00:22:14,610 --> 00:22:15,890
Yes, Director Tak.

358
00:22:16,010 --> 00:22:17,800
What brings you here?

359
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:20,610
It's been a while since I had some free time,
so I wanted to see Prosecutor Ju.

360
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:21,830
But he wasn't around.

361
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,940
I thought he might be here.

362
00:22:24,740 --> 00:22:26,500
Didn't you visit me last week?

363
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:30,050
It breaks my heart to hear you say that.

364
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:34,490
Anyway,

365
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:37,460
are you two
investigating something together?

366
00:22:38,090 --> 00:22:39,610
Ah.

367
00:22:39,770 --> 00:22:41,100
It's Oh Jayeon.

368
00:22:41,370 --> 00:22:44,380
I came to ask Prosecutor Yoon
to request an arrest warrant.

369
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:47,560
Ah, the one who caused
a disturbance at the police station.

370
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:48,220
Yes.

371
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:50,200
I heard it was related to drugs.

372
00:22:50,580 --> 00:22:53,130
Do we have enough evidence
to go after her?

373
00:22:53,430 --> 00:22:58,110
Yes. She seems to be related
to the murder of the Koryoin.

374
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,030
The type of drug is the same.

375
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:04,970
It's also possible that the drugs in circulation
later flowed into Oh Jayeon's hands.

376
00:23:05,370 --> 00:23:06,170
Prosecutor Yoon.

377
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:07,060
Yes.

378
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:09,200
Do you have other intentions?

379
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:13,580
Not at all, Director Tak.

380
00:23:14,940 --> 00:23:17,360
Don't act on impulse.

381
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:19,090
That's what I'm afraid of.

382
00:23:19,370 --> 00:23:23,130
Neither of you
can look at this case objectively.

383
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:28,170
I'm not acting on this
out of personal emotions.

384
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:33,270
Just because Oh Jayeon was
kicked out of the Ohsong Group

385
00:23:33,270 --> 00:23:35,750
doesn't mean she is no longer
a member of the Oh family.

386
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:38,530
If the prosecution goes wrong,
the district office will be disgraced.

387
00:23:38,530 --> 00:23:40,770
If we fail, the Supreme Prosecutors' Office
will pressure us.

388
00:23:40,770 --> 00:23:43,030
So, what I mean is,
don't mess with her rashly.

389
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:44,030
Don't let your imagination run wild.

390
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:48,180
Only look at the evidence
in front of you. Investigate objectively.

391
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:53,470
I... don't want you to get hurt.

392
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:57,560
I don't want to lose
my own people anymore.

393
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:01,180
Yes.

394
00:24:01,390 --> 00:24:03,670
Yes. I'll keep that in mind.

395
00:24:04,420 --> 00:24:05,460
Also,

396
00:24:05,670 --> 00:24:08,330
that Supervisor Lee Chaeha
you cherish so much,

397
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:13,190
it won't do any good
to get him involved in this.

398
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:16,630
Okay, I'll take good care of him.

399
00:24:26,410 --> 00:24:29,370
[Ohsong Construction]

400
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:41,540
I heard Jayeon got into trouble.

401
00:24:41,810 --> 00:24:44,340
I heard she used meth.

402
00:24:46,190 --> 00:24:48,660
She still thinks she's a child.

403
00:24:48,910 --> 00:24:51,240
I hope she comes to her senses soon.

404
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,320
I will fully cooperate with you.

405
00:24:53,490 --> 00:24:54,840
Thank you.

406
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:59,900
A few months ago, the dealer
suspected of selling drugs to Oh Jayeon

407
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:02,010
was found dead.

408
00:25:02,150 --> 00:25:06,480
Are you saying Jayeon... dumped the body?

409
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,890
We can't give you a definite answer
at this stage.

410
00:25:10,070 --> 00:25:15,520
Do you know if Oh Jayeon
had any possible accomplices around her?

411
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:16,930
Such as someone she hired,

412
00:25:16,930 --> 00:25:18,000
or maybe a friend?

413
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:21,130
Her reputation isn't that good,

414
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:24,660
and she's not generous enough
to pay her subordinates well.

415
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:30,630
I heard she really wants
to return to Ohsong.

416
00:25:30,770 --> 00:25:34,430
I wonder why she has
such a terrible relationship with her father.

417
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:37,280
After all, she's always causing trouble.

418
00:25:39,450 --> 00:25:40,640
Ah.

419
00:25:41,190 --> 00:25:44,860
It seems she got worse
after that incident.

420
00:25:45,140 --> 00:25:47,120
That incident?

421
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,600
That was a long time ago.

422
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:03,840
She had a boyfriend
she dated since high school.

423
00:26:04,530 --> 00:26:07,750
She got pregnant in her 20s,
but later had an abortion.

424
00:26:08,070 --> 00:26:11,270
No matter how my dad tried
to break them up, it didn't work.

425
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,350
Why did he want to break them up?

426
00:26:14,430 --> 00:26:17,190
Because that man killed his own sister.

427
00:26:19,770 --> 00:26:21,450
But it was just a rumor.

428
00:26:21,570 --> 00:26:25,230
Due to a lack of evidence,
he was eventually cleared of suspicion.

429
00:26:25,410 --> 00:26:29,240
But my dad kept harping on
about how he's the child of a murderer,

430
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:32,200
and forced Jayeon to abort the baby.

431
00:26:34,130 --> 00:26:37,420
Then, the ultimate measure my dad took

432
00:26:37,540 --> 00:26:39,850
was sending that man abroad.

433
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,560
When Jayeon found out,

434
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:44,500
she went completely crazy.

435
00:26:45,070 --> 00:26:47,190
She stabbed my dad with a knife.

436
00:26:52,340 --> 00:26:54,150
Looking back,

437
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:57,900
it's entirely possible
she could kill someone.

438
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:01,080
She has anger management issues.

439
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:05,240
What happened to them after that?

440
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:08,880
Naturally, they broke up.

441
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:13,840
Probably because my dad stated in his will

442
00:27:13,970 --> 00:27:15,880
that if she had any ties with that man,

443
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:18,610
she would be removed
from the list of inheritors.

444
00:27:19,170 --> 00:27:23,160
After that, both Jayeon and that man
started their own families.

445
00:27:24,330 --> 00:27:27,080
Even though
they were madly in love before.

446
00:27:30,250 --> 00:27:32,390
[National Forensic Service]

447
00:27:34,740 --> 00:27:36,710
Sorry, please excuse me.

448
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:42,440
Hello?

449
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,460
DNA?

450
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:46,340
The glove?

451
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:50,170
Right. We didn't find a match

452
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:52,100
in the ex-convict DNA database.

453
00:27:57,560 --> 00:28:00,940
This man Oh Jayeon used to love...

454
00:28:03,210 --> 00:28:05,610
What was his name?

455
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:10,990
He's right next to you.

456
00:28:12,020 --> 00:28:12,820
What?

457
00:28:12,990 --> 00:28:15,690
Fortunately, the surname that came out
of the analysis result is quite unique.

458
00:28:15,690 --> 00:28:16,940
Unique?

459
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:20,090
Yes.

460
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:22,500
-The surname is Tak.
-It's Tak Sungwoon.

461
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,900
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

462
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:39,900
[Next Episode]

463
00:28:36,100 --> 00:28:37,830
That Supervisor Lee Chaeha...

464
00:28:37,990 --> 00:28:40,320
Having Lee Gilyoung's son
investigate Oh Jayeon

465
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,680
makes me feel uneasy.

466
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:44,560
You're hoping
it wasn't Director Tak, right?

467
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:47,250
I completely understand how you feel.

468
00:28:47,390 --> 00:28:48,790
Don't make wild guesses,

469
00:28:48,820 --> 00:28:50,820
and don't project yourself onto me.

470
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:57,990
Seems like you had a good time.

471
00:28:57,990 --> 00:28:59,320
Were you waiting for me?

472
00:28:59,390 --> 00:29:00,440
I'm leaving.

473
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:04,490
I don't want to be held by a hand
that happily waved at other men.

